<subSubSection id="52788498C7257FBAA86B109A10266DF9" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" type="notes">
<paragraph id="3B206070EE49D901B32FC515A2504692" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CDF476BF60A7D8D4BFA5E27FE96F601A" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">
Recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="5EB4668A569DE8FE44DA158679D1E609" author="Erlandsson, S" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="11 - 93" refId="B6" refString="Erlandsson, S, 1972. Hymenoptera Aculeata from the European parts of the Mediterranean Countries. Eos Madrid 48: 11 - 93" title="Hymenoptera Aculeata from the European parts of the Mediterranean Countries." volume="48" year="1972">Erlandsson (1972)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="3C089A3195D9A820D835BC39A53514E4" author="Schembri, SP" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" pagination="90 - 93" refId="B16" refString="Schembri, SP, 1980. Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata). Bollettino della Societa' Entomologica Italiana 112 (4-6): 90 - 93" title="Vespoidea from the Maltese Islands (Hymenoptera Aculeata)." volume="112" year="1980">Schembri (1980)</bibRefCitation>
. This 
<normalizedToken id="FB57C922A09718E522A7C769BC33D5F2" originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
distributional range includes much of southern Europe as well as a few northern countries such as Austria and Slovakia; it also occurs in North Africa and the Middle East. 
<taxonomicName id="2E40AB44AD4ACF8DCC67287ACCA6CAB4" baseAuthorityName="de Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Leptochilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptochilus regulus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regulus">
<emphasis id="97418CA7BCF4971855AA4EFA9C76A082" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="201">Leptochilus regulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is another eumenine whose colouration may vary greatly between individuals; some lacking much of the yellow markings from the clypeus down to the second tergite, instead having those areas completely black (
<bibRefCitation id="3487F971B5FF65F7BAF4B5C8AEAEC9A0" author="Gusenleitner, J" journalOrPublisher="Eos Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="201" refId="B7" refString="Gusenleitner, J, 1993. Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 1: Die Gattung Leptochilus SAUSSURE 1852. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 25/2: 745-769." title="Bestimmungstabellen mittel- und suedeuropaeischer Eumeniden (Vespoidea, Hymenoptera) Teil 1: Die Gattung Leptochilus SAUSSURE 1852. Linzer Biologische Beitraege 25 / 2: 745 - 769." year="1993">Gusenleitner 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
